[2026-03-18T17:36:58.864Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SEdwuwj8Pgugo8BK2RBhwd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n     2→// Filtering HTTP CONNECT proxy for per-persona network policies\n     3→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n     4→\n     5→import http from 'node:http';\n     6→import net from 'node:net';\n     7→import type { Duplex } from 'node:stream';\n     8→import type { Logger } from 'pino';\n     9→import { type NetworkPolicyRule, isAllowed, type NetworkPolicy } from '@dac-cloud/shared';\n    10→\n    11→export interface ProxyHandle {\n    12→  port: number;\n    13→  cleanup: () => void;\n    14→}\n    15→\n    16→export async function startFilterProxy(\n    17→  policy: NetworkPolicy,\n    18→  logger: Logger,\n    19→  executionId: string,\n    20→): Promise<ProxyHandle> {\n    21→  const activeSockets = new Set<net.Socket | Duplex>();\n    22→  let allowedCount = 0;\n    23→  let blockedCount = 0;\n    24→\n    25→  const server = http.createServer((_req, res) => {\n    26→    // Non-CONNECT requests through proxy — check and forward or reject\n    27→    const url = _req.url;\n    28→    if (!url) { res.writeHead(400).end(); return; }\n    29→    try {\n    30→      const parsed = new URL(url);\n    31→      const port = parseInt(parsed.port, 10) || (parsed.protocol === 'https:' ? 443 : 80);\n    32→      if (!isAllowed(policy, parsed.hostname, port)) {\n    33→        blockedCount++;\n    34→        logger.warn({ executionId, host: parsed.hostname, port }, 'Proxy: blocked non-CONNECT request');\n    35→        res.writeHead(403, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' }).end('Blocked by network policy');\n    36→        return;\n    37→      }\n    38→      allowedCount++;\n    39→    } catch (err) {\n    40→      logger.warn({ err, executionId, operation: 'proxy_parse_url' }, 'Proxy URL parse error');\n    41→      res.writeHead(400).end();\n    42→      return;\n    43→    }\n    44→    // For allowed non-CONNECT, pass through (minimal — most traffic uses CONNECT)\n    45→    res.writeHead(501).end('Direct proxy not supported, use CONNECT');\n    46→  });\n    47→\n    48→  server.on('connect', (req, clientSocket, head) => {\n    49→    const target = req.url ?? '';\n    50→    let host: string;\n    51→    let port: number;\n    52→\n    53→    // Parse CONNECT target, handling both IPv4 \"host:port\" and IPv6 \"[::1]:port\"\n    54→    if (target.startsWith('[')) {\n    55→      const closeBracket = target.indexOf(']');\n    56→      host = closeBracket > 0 ? target.slice(1, closeBracket) : '';\n    57→      const portStr = closeBracket > 0 ? target.slice(closeBracket + 2) : '';\n    58→      port = parseInt(portStr, 10) || 443;\n    59→    } else {\n    60→      const lastColon = target.lastIndexOf(':');\n    61→      host = lastColon > 0 ? target.slice(0, lastColon) : target;\n    62→      port = lastColon > 0 ? parseInt(target.slice(lastColon + 1), 10) || 443 : 443;\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    if (!host || !isAllowed(policy, host, port)) {\n    66→      blockedCount++;\n    67→      logger.warn({ executionId, host, port }, 'Proxy: blocked CONNECT');\n    68→      clientSocket.write('HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n    69→      clientSocket.destroy();\n    70→      return;\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    allowedCount++;\n    74→\n    75→    const serverSocket = net.connect(port, host, () => {\n    76→      clientSocket.write('HTTP/1.1 200 Connection Established\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n    77→      serverSocket.write(head);\n    78→      serverSocket.pipe(clientSocket);\n    79→      clientSocket.pipe(serverSocket);\n    80→    });\n    81→\n    82→    activeSockets.add(clientSocket);\n    83→    activeSockets.add(serverSocket);\n    84→\n    85→    const removeSocket = (s: net.Socket | Duplex) => { activeSockets.delete(s); };\n    86→\n    87→    serverSocket.on('close', () => removeSocket(serverSocket));\n    88→    clientSocket.on('close', () => removeSocket(clientSocket));\n    89→\n    90→    serverSocket.on('error', (err) => {\n    91→      logger.error({ err, executionId, host, port }, 'Proxy: upstream connection error');\n    92→      clientSocket.destroy();\n    93→    });\n    94→\n    95→    clientSocket.on('error', (err) => {\n    96→      logger.warn({ err, executionId, host, port, operation: 'proxy_client_socket' }, 'Proxy: client socket error');\n    97→      serverSocket.destroy();\n    98→    });\n    99→  });\n   100→\n   101→  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n   102→    server.listen(0, '127.0.0.1', () => {\n   103→      const addr = server.address() as net.AddressInfo;\n   104→      logger.info({ executionId, port: addr.port, mode: policy.mode, rules: policy.allowedHosts?.length ?? 0 }, 'Network filter proxy started');\n   105→      resolve({\n   106→        port: addr.port,\n   107→        cleanup: () => {\n   108→          logger.info({ executionId, allowedCount, blockedCount }, 'Network filter proxy stopping');\n   109→          for (const socket of activeSockets) {\n   110→            socket.destroy();\n   111→          }\n   112→          activeSockets.clear();\n   113→          server.close();\n   114→        },\n   115→      });\n   116→    });\n   117→  });\n   118→}\n   119→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QCDZ6LeM8HYDps8f9rJDrU","session_id":"a6611918-5700-489e-b074-66c80e703fff","uuid":"e8060f5e-4676-46e1-b8d8-11baefb266c5","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:36:58.784Z"}
[2026-03-18T17:37:44.902Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"adb6389e107f9ee4f","tool_use_id":"toolu_01QCDZ6LeM8HYDps8f9rJDrU","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore worker package structure","usage":{"total_tokens":34291,"tool_uses":9,"duration_ms":55580},"uuid":"50616c98-6712-4fd4-97c1-cb8290b38a2a","session_id":"a6611918-5700-489e-b074-66c80e703fff"}
[2026-03-18T17:37:44.902Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QCDZ6LeM8HYDps8f9rJDrU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've now read all the source files in the worker package. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Worker Package (`packages/worker/src/`) - Comprehensive Summary\n\n### File Structure Overview\n\nThe worker package contains 8 TypeScript source files that work together to create an autonomous execution agent that connects to an orchestrator via WebSocket, receives execution assignments, manages sandboxed CLI environments, and reports back results.\n\n---\n\n### 1. **index.ts** - Main Entry Point & Orchestration\n**Purpose:** Bootstraps the worker, connects to orchestrator, and orchestrates the execution lifecycle.\n\n**Key Exports:**\n- `main()` - Async entry point that initializes the entire worker\n- Sets up credential cleanup mechanisms\n- Creates and manages the connection and executor instances\n\n**Key Responsibilities:**\n- Loads configuration via `loadConfig()`\n- Creates a `Connection` instance for WebSocket communication\n- Creates an `Executor` instance for running personas\n- Handles `ExecAssign` messages by delegating to executor\n- Tracks `currentExecutionId` to prevent concurrent executions\n- Manages callbacks for stdout, stderr, events, progress, and completion\n- Handles graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n- Manages execution cancellation and orchestrator-initiated shutdown with grace periods\n- Installs credential exit handler and sweeps orphaned credential files on startup\n\n**Shutdown Flow:**\n- Waits for in-flight execution to complete\n- Allows graceful period specified by orchestrator\n- Forces shutdown after grace period if needed\n- Calls `executor.waitForCleanup()` before exiting to ensure sandbox/credential cleanup\n\n---\n\n### 2. **config.ts** - Configuration Loading\n**Purpose:** Loads and validates worker configuration from environment variables.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface WorkerConfig {\n  orchestratorUrl: string;      // WebSocket URL to orchestrator\n  workerToken: string;          // Bearer token for authentication\n  workerId: string;             // Unique worker identifier (auto-generated if not set)\n  imageDigest: string;          // Image verification digest\n  claudeCliVersion: string;     // Claude CLI version\n  tlsCaPath: string;            // Path to CA cert for TLS\n  tlsCertPath: string;          // Path to client cert for TLS\n  tlsKeyPath: string;           // Path to client key for TLS\n  tlsRejectUnauthorized: boolean; // TLS verification strictness\n}\n\nfunction loadConfig(): WorkerConfig\n```\n\n**Key Logic:**\n- `required()` helper validates essential env vars (ORCHESTRATOR_URL, WORKER_TOKEN)\n- Optional vars with defaults (WORKER_ID auto-generated via nanoid)\n- TLS config entirely optional\n- Configuration is immutable after loading\n\n---\n\n### 3. **connection.ts** - WebSocket Connection Management\n**Purpose:** Manages bidirectional WebSocket communication with orchestrator.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface WorkerTlsConfig {\n  caPath, certPath, keyPath, rejectUnauthorized: boolean\n}\n\ninterface ConnectionCallbacks {\n  onAssign(msg: ExecAssign): void;\n  onCancel(msg: ExecCancel): void;\n  onShutdown(msg: OrchestratorShutdown): void;\n}\n\nclass Connection {\n  connect(): void\n  disconnect(): void\n  isConnected(): boolean\n  send(msg: WorkerMessage): boolean\n  sendReady(): void\n  sendBusy(executionId, reason): void\n  sendStdout(executionId, chunk): void\n  sendStderr(executionId, chunk): void\n  sendComplete(executionId, status, exitCode, durationMs, sessionId?, totalCostUsd?, phaseTimings?): void\n  sendProgress(executionId, phase, percent, detail?): void\n  sendEvent(executionId, eventType, payload): void\n}\n```\n\n**Connection Lifecycle:**\n- **Connect Phase:**\n  - Establishes WebSocket with bearer token authentication\n  - Sends `hello` message with worker capabilities: `['claude-cli', 'node', 'git', 'network-policy']`\n  - Starts 30-second heartbeat interval\n  \n- **Message Handling:**\n  - `ack` - Connection acknowledged, sends ready\n  - `assign` - Execution task assignment → delegates to callback\n  - `cancel` - Cancel current execution → delegates to callback\n  - `shutdown` - Graceful shutdown → delegates to callback\n  - `heartbeat` - Keep-alive (no action needed)\n  \n- **Reconnection Strategy:**\n  - Exponential backoff: 1s → 2s → 4s → ... → max 30s\n  - Automatically reconnects on disconnect\n  - Stops reconnecting if shutdown was triggered\n\n- **TLS Support:**\n  - Optional client certificates for wss:// connections\n  - CA cert validation (default: enabled)\n  - Caches TLS options at construction time\n\n---\n\n### 4. **executor.ts** - Execution Engine\n**Purpose:** Manages the lifecycle of a single execution, from sandbox setup to cleanup.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface ExecutorCallbacks {\n  onStdout(chunk: string, timestamp: number): void;\n  onStderr(chunk: string, timestamp: number): void;\n  onEvent(eventType, payload): void;\n  onProgress(phase, percent, detail?): void;\n  onComplete(status, exitCode, durationMs, sessionId?, totalCostUsd?, phaseTimings?): void;\n}\n\nclass Executor {\n  isBusy(): boolean\n  execute(assignment: ExecAssign, callbacks): Promise<void>\n  kill(): void\n  waitForCleanup(timeoutMs?): Promise<void>\n}\n```\n\n**Execution Pipeline:**\n\n1. **Setup Phase:**\n   - `prepareSandbox()` - Creates isolated directory structure\n   - `startFilterProxy()` (if network policy) - HTTP CONNECT proxy for allow-list enforcement\n   - `injectCredentialsViaFile()` - Writes credentials to tmpfs-backed file\n\n2. **Execution Phase:**\n   - `spawn()` child process with claude CLI\n   - Pipes prompt to stdin\n   - Sets execution timeout (configurable)\n   - Streams stdout/stderr in real-time\n\n3. **Stream Processing:**\n   - Uses `LineBuffer` to accumulate partial lines\n   - Calls `extractStreamEvents()` to parse persona protocol messages\n   - Extracts sessionId, totalCostUsd, persona events, progress\n\n4. **Cleanup Phase:**\n   - Kills child process (SIGTERM → SIGKILL after 5s)\n   - Cleans up credential file\n   - Stops proxy\n   - Removes sandbox directory\n   - Measures phase timings (sandboxSetup, credentialInjection, proxyStartup, cliRuntime, cleanup)\n\n**Status Determination:**\n- `cancelled` if process was killed\n- `completed` if exit code = 0\n- `failed` if exit code ≠ 0\n\n**Safety Features:**\n- `waitForCleanup()` enforces max 10s timeout for cleanup\n- Only one execution at a time (checked via `isBusy()`)\n- Finally block ensures cleanup even on errors\n- Graceful handling of orphaned processes\n\n---\n\n### 5. **parser.ts** - Stream Event Extraction\n**Purpose:** Parses persona protocol messages and progress events from stdout streams.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface StreamEvents {\n  raw: string;\n  type?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  totalCostUsd?: number;\n  personaEvents: PersonaProtocolEvent[];\n  progress: ProgressInfo | null;\n}\n\ninterface PersonaProtocolEvent {\n  eventType: 'manual_review' | 'user_message' | 'persona_action' | 'emit_event';\n  payload: unknown;\n}\n\nfunction extractStreamEvents(line: string, logger): StreamEvents\nclass LineBuffer {\n  push(chunk: string): string[]\n  flush(): string[]\n}\n```\n\n**Parsing Logic:**\n\n1. **Line Buffering:** Accumulates chunks until newline found\n2. **JSON Detection:** Attempts to parse each complete line as JSON\n3. **Event Extraction:**\n   - `sessionId` - From `parsed.session_id` or `parsed.result.session_id`\n   - `totalCostUsd` - From result messages with type='result'\n   - **Persona Events** - From assistant message content blocks:\n     - Extracts JSON objects from text blocks\n     - Looks for keys: `manual_review`, `user_message`, `persona_action`, `emit_event`\n   - **Progress Events** - Extracts `{progress: {phase, percent, detail}}`\n   - Clamps progress percent to 0-100\n\n**JSON Pattern:** Uses regex `/\\{[^{}]*(?:\\{[^{}]*\\}[^{}]*)*\\}/g` to find nested JSON objects safely\n\n---\n\n### 6. **sandbox.ts** - Execution Sandboxing\n**Purpose:** Provides process isolation via bubblewrap (bwrap) or fallback per-execution HOME.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface SandboxConfig {\n  executionId: string;\n  env: Record<string, string>;\n  accessToken?: string;\n  networkAccess: boolean;\n  networkPolicy?: NetworkPolicy;\n  timeoutMs: number;\n  maxBudgetUsd?: number;\n  maxTurns?: number;\n}\n\ninterface SandboxResult {\n  command: string;\n  args: string[];\n  env: Record<string, string>;\n  cwd: string;\n  sandboxDir: string;\n  proxyRequired?: boolean;\n}\n\nfunction isSandboxAvailable(): boolean\nfunction prepareSandbox(config, logger): SandboxResult\nfunction cleanupSandbox(sandboxDir, logger): void\n```\n\n**Sandbox Modes:**\n\n1. **bwrap Mode (Linux with bubblewrap):**\n   - Full namespace isolation: PID, UTS, network\n   - Read-only system mounts: `/usr`, `/bin`, `/etc`, etc.\n   - Per-execution writable mounts:\n     - `/home/exec` (HOME) - claude config, credentials\n     - `/workspace` (work dir)\n     - `/tmp` (tmpdir)\n   - New session isolation with `--new-session`\n   - Network isolation by default (unless policy is allow-list)\n   - Proxy environment variables injected if network policy enabled\n\n2. **Fallback Mode (no namespace isolation):**\n   - Per-execution HOME and TMPDIR\n   - **Cannot enforce network policies** - requires bwrap for namespace isolation\n   - Throws error if network policy is present\n\n**Sandbox Directory Structure:**\n```\ndac-sandbox-{executionId}/\n├── home/\n│   ├── .claude/\n│   │   ├── .credentials.json (OAuth credentials if present)\n│   │   └── (onboarding complete marker)\n│   └── .claude.json\n├── work/\n└── tmp/\n```\n\n**Environment Setup:**\n- Clean environment (doesn't inherit from process.env)\n- Minimal PATH, NODE_ENV=production, LANG=en_US.UTF-8\n- Credential env vars removed (injected via file instead)\n- CLAUDECODE explicitly unset (prevents nested sessions)\n- OAuth tokens written to `.credentials.json` if present (sk-ant-oat* pattern)\n- Non-OAuth API keys passed via ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var\n\n**CLI Argument Building:**\n- Uses `buildCliArgs()` from shared package\n- Supports maxBudgetUsd and maxTurns configuration\n- Static bwrap args cached at module init time for performance\n\n---\n\n### 7. **credentialInjector.ts** - Secure Credential Management\n**Purpose:** Securely handles credential lifecycle to prevent exposure via process inspection.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface InjectedCredentials {\n  credentialFilePath: string;\n  envPointerKey: string;           // 'DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE'\n  cleanup(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\nfunction installCredentialExitHandler(logger): void\nfunction sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles(logger): Promise<number>\nfunction injectCredentialsViaFile(env, executionId, logger): Promise<InjectedCredentials>\nfunction getActiveCredentialFileCount(): number\n```\n\n**Credential Flow:**\n\n1. **Identification:**\n   - Collects env vars matching patterns: `CONNECTOR_*`, `*TOKEN*`, `*SECRET*`, `*PASSWORD*`, `*API_KEY*`\n   - Also includes `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n\n2. **Storage (Linux-first approach):**\n   - Prefers `/dev/shm` (tmpfs, memory-backed, never hits disk)\n   - Falls back to `os.tmpdir()` on other platforms\n   - File format: `{tmpDir}/dac-creds-{executionId}-{randomHex}.json`\n   - File permissions: 0o600 (owner read/write only)\n\n3. **Injection:**\n   - Writes credentials to temporary file asynchronously\n   - Removes credential keys from env dict\n   - Sets `DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE` env var pointing to file\n   - Child process reads from file instead of inspecting environment\n\n4. **Cleanup:**\n   - Active credential files tracked in Set\n   - Exit handler runs on 'exit' event (catches crashes)\n   - Sweeps orphaned files on startup (max age: 2 minutes)\n   - Async cleanup after execution completes\n\n**Safety Benefits:**\n- Prevents credential exposure via `/proc/{pid}/environ` or `ps auxe`\n- Credentials never in environment strings\n- tmpfs storage never touches disk on Linux\n- Exit handler catches abnormal crashes\n\n---\n\n### 8. **networkProxy.ts** - Network Policy Enforcement\n**Purpose:** Implements HTTP CONNECT proxy to enforce allow-list network policies.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface ProxyHandle {\n  port: number;\n  cleanup: () => void;\n}\n\nasync function startFilterProxy(policy, logger, executionId): Promise<ProxyHandle>\n```\n\n**Proxy Mechanism:**\n\n1. **Listening:**\n   - HTTP CONNECT proxy on 127.0.0.1 (random free port)\n   - Set via HTTP_PROXY, HTTPS_PROXY, http_proxy, https_proxy env vars\n\n2. **Request Filtering:**\n   - **Non-CONNECT requests:** Parse URL, check via `isAllowed()`, reject with 403\n   - **CONNECT requests:** Tunnel establishment\n     - Parses target (handles both IPv4 `host:port` and IPv6 `[::1]:port`)\n     - Checks policy via `isAllowed(policy, host, port)`\n     - Blocks with HTTP 403 if not allowed\n     - Establishes transparent tunnel if allowed\n\n3. **Connection Management:**\n   - Tracks all active sockets\n   - Pipes bidirectional data between client and server\n   - Cleans up on close/error\n   - Logs connection errors\n\n4. **Policy Enforcement:**\n   - Uses shared `isAllowed()` function to check against policy rules\n   - Counts allowed vs blocked connections\n   - Logs warnings for blocked requests\n\n**Integration with Executor:**\n- Only started if `config.networkPolicy?.mode === 'allow-list'`\n- Proxy URL injected into sandbox environment\n- Cleaned up after execution completes\n\n---\n\n### Execution Flow Diagram\n\n```\nWorker Startup\n  ├─ loadConfig() → WorkerConfig\n  ├─ installCredentialExitHandler()\n  ├─ sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles()\n  ├─ new Connection() → WebSocket connection\n  ├─ new Executor()\n  └─ connection.connect() → \"hello\" message\n\nOrchestrator Assignment (ExecAssign)\n  ├─ Check if currentExecutionId or executor.isBusy() → sendBusy() if true\n  ├─ Set currentExecutionId\n  └─ executor.execute(assignment, callbacks)\n\nExecution Lifecycle\n  ├─ prepareSandbox()\n  │   ├─ createSandboxDir()\n  │   ├─ buildCleanEnv()\n  │   └─ If bwrap available:\n  │       ├─ Full namespace isolation\n  │       └─ Return bwrap command + args\n  │   └─ Else:\n  │       └─ Return claude command + args (no namespace isolation)\n  │\n  ├─ If network policy:\n  │   ├─ startFilterProxy() → HTTP CONNECT proxy\n  │   └─ Inject proxy URL via HTTP_PROXY env vars\n  │\n  ├─ injectCredentialsViaFile()\n  │   ├─ Write credentials to /dev/shm or /tmp\n  │   └─ Set DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE env var\n  │\n  ├─ spawn(command, args, {env, cwd, stdio})\n  ├─ Write prompt to stdin\n  ├─ Set execution timeout\n  │\n  ├─ Stream Processing (stdout/stderr):\n  │   ├─ LineBuffer accumulates data\n  │   ├─ extractStreamEvents(line) parses JSON\n  │   │   ├─ Extract sessionId, totalCostUsd\n  │   │   ├─ Extract persona protocol events\n  │   │   └─ Extract progress events\n  │   └─ Callbacks: onStdout, onStderr, onEvent, onProgress\n  │\n  ├─ Wait for process exit\n  ├─ Determine status: cancelled | completed | failed\n  │\n  └─ Cleanup (finally block):\n      ├─ Kill process (SIGTERM → SIGKILL after 5s)\n      ├─ Delete credential file\n      ├─ Proxy cleanup\n      ├─ Remove sandbox directory\n      └─ Record phase timings\n\nCompletion Callback (onComplete)\n  ├─ sendComplete() → Orchestrator\n  ├─ currentExecutionId = null\n  └─ sendReady() → Available for next assignment\n\nShutdown Flow\n  ├─ Orchestrator sends \"shutdown\" message\n  ├─ If currentExecutionId: Wait for execution to finish (with grace period)\n  ├─ executor.waitForCleanup() → max 10s\n  ├─ connection.disconnect()\n  └─ process.exit(0)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Callback-Based Architecture:** All async operations use callbacks rather than promises (enables streaming)\n2. **Cleanup Guarantees:** Finally blocks + exit handlers ensure resources cleaned up even on crashes\n3. **Phase Timing Tracking:** Records time spent in setup, injection, proxy, runtime, cleanup for observability\n4. **Graceful Degradation:** Falls back to per-HOME sandbox when bwrap unavailable (except with network policies)\n5. **Tmpfs Preference:** Stores credentials in memory-backed storage on Linux to avoid disk exposure\n6. **Stream Event Extraction:** Parses persona protocol messages embedded in stdout JSON blocks\n7. **Single-Task Executor:** Only one execution at a time, prevents resource contention\n\n---\n\n### Health/Status Mechanisms\n\n1. **Heartbeat:** 30-second intervals from worker to orchestrator (keep-alive)\n2. **Ready Signal:** Sent after hello ack and after execution completion\n3. **Busy Signal:** Sent immediately if assignment arrives while executing\n4. **Active Credential File Count:** Gauge metric via `getActiveCredentialFileCount()`\n5. **Phase Timings:** Per-execution breakdown of where time is spent\n6. **Logging:** Comprehensive structured logging via pino (executionId, personaId, phase, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### Critical Paths & Error Handling\n\n- **Timeout Handling:** Sets execution timeout before spawn, kills process on expiry\n- **Process Death:** Catches spawn errors and process errors, resolves with exit code 1\n- **Network Proxy Errors:** Upstream/client socket errors logged, connections destroyed\n- **Credential File Leaks:** Exit handler + sweep mechanism prevents accumulation\n- **Sandbox Cleanup Failures:** Logged but not fatal, continues with shutdown\n\nThis architecture creates a robust, isolated execution environment with comprehensive security, observability, and graceful degradation."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb6389e107f9ee4f (use SendMessage with to: 'adb6389e107f9ee4f' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 39179\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 55582</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6611918-5700-489e-b074-66c80e703fff","uuid":"4507c0d9-7db0-418b-a155-12ebc6c4f71d","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:37:44.809Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the worker package in packages/worker/src/ thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full file structure and what each file does\n2. How the worker connects via WebSocket (connection.ts)\n3. How executions work (executor.ts)\n4. The current config (config.ts)\n5. The index.ts entry point - how the worker starts up\n6. Any existing health/status mechanisms\n7. The sandbox.ts file if it exists\n\nRead all the source files in packages/worker/src/ and provide a comprehensive summary of each file's exports, key functions, and how they relate to each other.","agentId":"adb6389e107f9ee4f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've now read all the source files in the worker package. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Worker Package (`packages/worker/src/`) - Comprehensive Summary\n\n### File Structure Overview\n\nThe worker package contains 8 TypeScript source files that work together to create an autonomous execution agent that connects to an orchestrator via WebSocket, receives execution assignments, manages sandboxed CLI environments, and reports back results.\n\n---\n\n### 1. **index.ts** - Main Entry Point & Orchestration\n**Purpose:** Bootstraps the worker, connects to orchestrator, and orchestrates the execution lifecycle.\n\n**Key Exports:**\n- `main()` - Async entry point that initializes the entire worker\n- Sets up credential cleanup mechanisms\n- Creates and manages the connection and executor instances\n\n**Key Responsibilities:**\n- Loads configuration via `loadConfig()`\n- Creates a `Connection` instance for WebSocket communication\n- Creates an `Executor` instance for running personas\n- Handles `ExecAssign` messages by delegating to executor\n- Tracks `currentExecutionId` to prevent concurrent executions\n- Manages callbacks for stdout, stderr, events, progress, and completion\n- Handles graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n- Manages execution cancellation and orchestrator-initiated shutdown with grace periods\n- Installs credential exit handler and sweeps orphaned credential files on startup\n\n**Shutdown Flow:**\n- Waits for in-flight execution to complete\n- Allows graceful period specified by orchestrator\n- Forces shutdown after grace period if needed\n- Calls `executor.waitForCleanup()` before exiting to ensure sandbox/credential cleanup\n\n---\n\n### 2. **config.ts** - Configuration Loading\n**Purpose:** Loads and validates worker configuration from environment variables.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface WorkerConfig {\n  orchestratorUrl: string;      // WebSocket URL to orchestrator\n  workerToken: string;          // Bearer token for authentication\n  workerId: string;             // Unique worker identifier (auto-generated if not set)\n  imageDigest: string;          // Image verification digest\n  claudeCliVersion: string;     // Claude CLI version\n  tlsCaPath: string;            // Path to CA cert for TLS\n  tlsCertPath: string;          // Path to client cert for TLS\n  tlsKeyPath: string;           // Path to client key for TLS\n  tlsRejectUnauthorized: boolean; // TLS verification strictness\n}\n\nfunction loadConfig(): WorkerConfig\n```\n\n**Key Logic:**\n- `required()` helper validates essential env vars (ORCHESTRATOR_URL, WORKER_TOKEN)\n- Optional vars with defaults (WORKER_ID auto-generated via nanoid)\n- TLS config entirely optional\n- Configuration is immutable after loading\n\n---\n\n### 3. **connection.ts** - WebSocket Connection Management\n**Purpose:** Manages bidirectional WebSocket communication with orchestrator.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface WorkerTlsConfig {\n  caPath, certPath, keyPath, rejectUnauthorized: boolean\n}\n\ninterface ConnectionCallbacks {\n  onAssign(msg: ExecAssign): void;\n  onCancel(msg: ExecCancel): void;\n  onShutdown(msg: OrchestratorShutdown): void;\n}\n\nclass Connection {\n  connect(): void\n  disconnect(): void\n  isConnected(): boolean\n  send(msg: WorkerMessage): boolean\n  sendReady(): void\n  sendBusy(executionId, reason): void\n  sendStdout(executionId, chunk): void\n  sendStderr(executionId, chunk): void\n  sendComplete(executionId, status, exitCode, durationMs, sessionId?, totalCostUsd?, phaseTimings?): void\n  sendProgress(executionId, phase, percent, detail?): void\n  sendEvent(executionId, eventType, payload): void\n}\n```\n\n**Connection Lifecycle:**\n- **Connect Phase:**\n  - Establishes WebSocket with bearer token authentication\n  - Sends `hello` message with worker capabilities: `['claude-cli', 'node', 'git', 'network-policy']`\n  - Starts 30-second heartbeat interval\n  \n- **Message Handling:**\n  - `ack` - Connection acknowledged, sends ready\n  - `assign` - Execution task assignment → delegates to callback\n  - `cancel` - Cancel current execution → delegates to callback\n  - `shutdown` - Graceful shutdown → delegates to callback\n  - `heartbeat` - Keep-alive (no action needed)\n  \n- **Reconnection Strategy:**\n  - Exponential backoff: 1s → 2s → 4s → ... → max 30s\n  - Automatically reconnects on disconnect\n  - Stops reconnecting if shutdown was triggered\n\n- **TLS Support:**\n  - Optional client certificates for wss:// connections\n  - CA cert validation (default: enabled)\n  - Caches TLS options at construction time\n\n---\n\n### 4. **executor.ts** - Execution Engine\n**Purpose:** Manages the lifecycle of a single execution, from sandbox setup to cleanup.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface ExecutorCallbacks {\n  onStdout(chunk: string, timestamp: number): void;\n  onStderr(chunk: string, timestamp: number): void;\n  onEvent(eventType, payload): void;\n  onProgress(phase, percent, detail?): void;\n  onComplete(status, exitCode, durationMs, sessionId?, totalCostUsd?, phaseTimings?): void;\n}\n\nclass Executor {\n  isBusy(): boolean\n  execute(assignment: ExecAssign, callbacks): Promise<void>\n  kill(): void\n  waitForCleanup(timeoutMs?): Promise<void>\n}\n```\n\n**Execution Pipeline:**\n\n1. **Setup Phase:**\n   - `prepareSandbox()` - Creates isolated directory structure\n   - `startFilterProxy()` (if network policy) - HTTP CONNECT proxy for allow-list enforcement\n   - `injectCredentialsViaFile()` - Writes credentials to tmpfs-backed file\n\n2. **Execution Phase:**\n   - `spawn()` child process with claude CLI\n   - Pipes prompt to stdin\n   - Sets execution timeout (configurable)\n   - Streams stdout/stderr in real-time\n\n3. **Stream Processing:**\n   - Uses `LineBuffer` to accumulate partial lines\n   - Calls `extractStreamEvents()` to parse persona protocol messages\n   - Extracts sessionId, totalCostUsd, persona events, progress\n\n4. **Cleanup Phase:**\n   - Kills child process (SIGTERM → SIGKILL after 5s)\n   - Cleans up credential file\n   - Stops proxy\n   - Removes sandbox directory\n   - Measures phase timings (sandboxSetup, credentialInjection, proxyStartup, cliRuntime, cleanup)\n\n**Status Determination:**\n- `cancelled` if process was killed\n- `completed` if exit code = 0\n- `failed` if exit code ≠ 0\n\n**Safety Features:**\n- `waitForCleanup()` enforces max 10s timeout for cleanup\n- Only one execution at a time (checked via `isBusy()`)\n- Finally block ensures cleanup even on errors\n- Graceful handling of orphaned processes\n\n---\n\n### 5. **parser.ts** - Stream Event Extraction\n**Purpose:** Parses persona protocol messages and progress events from stdout streams.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface StreamEvents {\n  raw: string;\n  type?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  totalCostUsd?: number;\n  personaEvents: PersonaProtocolEvent[];\n  progress: ProgressInfo | null;\n}\n\ninterface PersonaProtocolEvent {\n  eventType: 'manual_review' | 'user_message' | 'persona_action' | 'emit_event';\n  payload: unknown;\n}\n\nfunction extractStreamEvents(line: string, logger): StreamEvents\nclass LineBuffer {\n  push(chunk: string): string[]\n  flush(): string[]\n}\n```\n\n**Parsing Logic:**\n\n1. **Line Buffering:** Accumulates chunks until newline found\n2. **JSON Detection:** Attempts to parse each complete line as JSON\n3. **Event Extraction:**\n   - `sessionId` - From `parsed.session_id` or `parsed.result.session_id`\n   - `totalCostUsd` - From result messages with type='result'\n   - **Persona Events** - From assistant message content blocks:\n     - Extracts JSON objects from text blocks\n     - Looks for keys: `manual_review`, `user_message`, `persona_action`, `emit_event`\n   - **Progress Events** - Extracts `{progress: {phase, percent, detail}}`\n   - Clamps progress percent to 0-100\n\n**JSON Pattern:** Uses regex `/\\{[^{}]*(?:\\{[^{}]*\\}[^{}]*)*\\}/g` to find nested JSON objects safely\n\n---\n\n### 6. **sandbox.ts** - Execution Sandboxing\n**Purpose:** Provides process isolation via bubblewrap (bwrap) or fallback per-execution HOME.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface SandboxConfig {\n  executionId: string;\n  env: Record<string, string>;\n  accessToken?: string;\n  networkAccess: boolean;\n  networkPolicy?: NetworkPolicy;\n  timeoutMs: number;\n  maxBudgetUsd?: number;\n  maxTurns?: number;\n}\n\ninterface SandboxResult {\n  command: string;\n  args: string[];\n  env: Record<string, string>;\n  cwd: string;\n  sandboxDir: string;\n  proxyRequired?: boolean;\n}\n\nfunction isSandboxAvailable(): boolean\nfunction prepareSandbox(config, logger): SandboxResult\nfunction cleanupSandbox(sandboxDir, logger): void\n```\n\n**Sandbox Modes:**\n\n1. **bwrap Mode (Linux with bubblewrap):**\n   - Full namespace isolation: PID, UTS, network\n   - Read-only system mounts: `/usr`, `/bin`, `/etc`, etc.\n   - Per-execution writable mounts:\n     - `/home/exec` (HOME) - claude config, credentials\n     - `/workspace` (work dir)\n     - `/tmp` (tmpdir)\n   - New session isolation with `--new-session`\n   - Network isolation by default (unless policy is allow-list)\n   - Proxy environment variables injected if network policy enabled\n\n2. **Fallback Mode (no namespace isolation):**\n   - Per-execution HOME and TMPDIR\n   - **Cannot enforce network policies** - requires bwrap for namespace isolation\n   - Throws error if network policy is present\n\n**Sandbox Directory Structure:**\n```\ndac-sandbox-{executionId}/\n├── home/\n│   ├── .claude/\n│   │   ├── .credentials.json (OAuth credentials if present)\n│   │   └── (onboarding complete marker)\n│   └── .claude.json\n├── work/\n└── tmp/\n```\n\n**Environment Setup:**\n- Clean environment (doesn't inherit from process.env)\n- Minimal PATH, NODE_ENV=production, LANG=en_US.UTF-8\n- Credential env vars removed (injected via file instead)\n- CLAUDECODE explicitly unset (prevents nested sessions)\n- OAuth tokens written to `.credentials.json` if present (sk-ant-oat* pattern)\n- Non-OAuth API keys passed via ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var\n\n**CLI Argument Building:**\n- Uses `buildCliArgs()` from shared package\n- Supports maxBudgetUsd and maxTurns configuration\n- Static bwrap args cached at module init time for performance\n\n---\n\n### 7. **credentialInjector.ts** - Secure Credential Management\n**Purpose:** Securely handles credential lifecycle to prevent exposure via process inspection.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface InjectedCredentials {\n  credentialFilePath: string;\n  envPointerKey: string;           // 'DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE'\n  cleanup(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\nfunction installCredentialExitHandler(logger): void\nfunction sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles(logger): Promise<number>\nfunction injectCredentialsViaFile(env, executionId, logger): Promise<InjectedCredentials>\nfunction getActiveCredentialFileCount(): number\n```\n\n**Credential Flow:**\n\n1. **Identification:**\n   - Collects env vars matching patterns: `CONNECTOR_*`, `*TOKEN*`, `*SECRET*`, `*PASSWORD*`, `*API_KEY*`\n   - Also includes `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n\n2. **Storage (Linux-first approach):**\n   - Prefers `/dev/shm` (tmpfs, memory-backed, never hits disk)\n   - Falls back to `os.tmpdir()` on other platforms\n   - File format: `{tmpDir}/dac-creds-{executionId}-{randomHex}.json`\n   - File permissions: 0o600 (owner read/write only)\n\n3. **Injection:**\n   - Writes credentials to temporary file asynchronously\n   - Removes credential keys from env dict\n   - Sets `DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE` env var pointing to file\n   - Child process reads from file instead of inspecting environment\n\n4. **Cleanup:**\n   - Active credential files tracked in Set\n   - Exit handler runs on 'exit' event (catches crashes)\n   - Sweeps orphaned files on startup (max age: 2 minutes)\n   - Async cleanup after execution completes\n\n**Safety Benefits:**\n- Prevents credential exposure via `/proc/{pid}/environ` or `ps auxe`\n- Credentials never in environment strings\n- tmpfs storage never touches disk on Linux\n- Exit handler catches abnormal crashes\n\n---\n\n### 8. **networkProxy.ts** - Network Policy Enforcement\n**Purpose:** Implements HTTP CONNECT proxy to enforce allow-list network policies.\n\n**Exports:**\n```typescript\ninterface ProxyHandle {\n  port: number;\n  cleanup: () => void;\n}\n\nasync function startFilterProxy(policy, logger, executionId): Promise<ProxyHandle>\n```\n\n**Proxy Mechanism:**\n\n1. **Listening:**\n   - HTTP CONNECT proxy on 127.0.0.1 (random free port)\n   - Set via HTTP_PROXY, HTTPS_PROXY, http_proxy, https_proxy env vars\n\n2. **Request Filtering:**\n   - **Non-CONNECT requests:** Parse URL, check via `isAllowed()`, reject with 403\n   - **CONNECT requests:** Tunnel establishment\n     - Parses target (handles both IPv4 `host:port` and IPv6 `[::1]:port`)\n     - Checks policy via `isAllowed(policy, host, port)`\n     - Blocks with HTTP 403 if not allowed\n     - Establishes transparent tunnel if allowed\n\n3. **Connection Management:**\n   - Tracks all active sockets\n   - Pipes bidirectional data between client and server\n   - Cleans up on close/error\n   - Logs connection errors\n\n4. **Policy Enforcement:**\n   - Uses shared `isAllowed()` function to check against policy rules\n   - Counts allowed vs blocked connections\n   - Logs warnings for blocked requests\n\n**Integration with Executor:**\n- Only started if `config.networkPolicy?.mode === 'allow-list'`\n- Proxy URL injected into sandbox environment\n- Cleaned up after execution completes\n\n---\n\n### Execution Flow Diagram\n\n```\nWorker Startup\n  ├─ loadConfig() → WorkerConfig\n  ├─ installCredentialExitHandler()\n  ├─ sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles()\n  ├─ new Connection() → WebSocket connection\n  ├─ new Executor()\n  └─ connection.connect() → \"hello\" message\n\nOrchestrator Assignment (ExecAssign)\n  ├─ Check if currentExecutionId or executor.isBusy() → sendBusy() if true\n  ├─ Set currentExecutionId\n  └─ executor.execute(assignment, callbacks)\n\nExecution Lifecycle\n  ├─ prepareSandbox()\n  │   ├─ createSandboxDir()\n  │   ├─ buildCleanEnv()\n  │   └─ If bwrap available:\n  │       ├─ Full namespace isolation\n  │       └─ Return bwrap command + args\n  │   └─ Else:\n  │       └─ Return claude command + args (no namespace isolation)\n  │\n  ├─ If network policy:\n  │   ├─ startFilterProxy() → HTTP CONNECT proxy\n  │   └─ Inject proxy URL via HTTP_PROXY env vars\n  │\n  ├─ injectCredentialsViaFile()\n  │   ├─ Write credentials to /dev/shm or /tmp\n  │   └─ Set DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE env var\n  │\n  ├─ spawn(command, args, {env, cwd, stdio})\n  ├─ Write prompt to stdin\n  ├─ Set execution timeout\n  │\n  ├─ Stream Processing (stdout/stderr):\n  │   ├─ LineBuffer accumulates data\n  │   ├─ extractStreamEvents(line) parses JSON\n  │   │   ├─ Extract sessionId, totalCostUsd\n  │   │   ├─ Extract persona protocol events\n  │   │   └─ Extract progress events\n  │   └─ Callbacks: onStdout, onStderr, onEvent, onProgress\n  │\n  ├─ Wait for process exit\n  ├─ Determine status: cancelled | completed | failed\n  │\n  └─ Cleanup (finally block):\n      ├─ Kill process (SIGTERM → SIGKILL after 5s)\n      ├─ Delete credential file\n      ├─ Proxy cleanup\n      ├─ Remove sandbox directory\n      └─ Record phase timings\n\nCompletion Callback (onComplete)\n  ├─ sendComplete() → Orchestrator\n  ├─ currentExecutionId = null\n  └─ sendReady() → Available for next assignment\n\nShutdown Flow\n  ├─ Orchestrator sends \"shutdown\" message\n  ├─ If currentExecutionId: Wait for execution to finish (with grace period)\n  ├─ executor.waitForCleanup() → max 10s\n  ├─ connection.disconnect()\n  └─ process.exit(0)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Callback-Based Architecture:** All async operations use callbacks rather than promises (enables streaming)\n2. **Cleanup Guarantees:** Finally blocks + exit handlers ensure resources cleaned up even on crashes\n3. **Phase Timing Tracking:** Records time spent in setup, injection, proxy, runtime, cleanup for observability\n4. **Graceful Degradation:** Falls back to per-HOME sandbox when bwrap unavailable (except with network policies)\n5. **Tmpfs Preference:** Stores credentials in memory-backed storage on Linux to avoid disk exposure\n6. **Stream Event Extraction:** Parses persona protocol messages embedded in stdout JSON blocks\n7. **Single-Task Executor:** Only one execution at a time, prevents resource contention\n\n---\n\n### Health/Status Mechanisms\n\n1. **Heartbeat:** 30-second intervals from worker to orchestrator (keep-alive)\n2. **Ready Signal:** Sent after hello ack and after execution completion\n3. **Busy Signal:** Sent immediately if assignment arrives while executing\n4. **Active Credential File Count:** Gauge metric via `getActiveCredentialFileCount()`\n5. **Phase Timings:** Per-execution breakdown of where time is spent\n6. **Logging:** Comprehensive structured logging via pino (executionId, personaId, phase, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### Critical Paths & Error Handling\n\n- **Timeout Handling:** Sets execution timeout before spawn, kills process on expiry\n- **Process Death:** Catches spawn errors and process errors, resolves with exit code 1\n- **Network Proxy Errors:** Upstream/client socket errors logged, connections destroyed\n- **Credential File Leaks:** Exit handler + sweep mechanism prevents accumulation\n- **Sandbox Cleanup Failures:** Logged but not fatal, continues with shutdown\n\nThis architecture creates a robust, isolated execution environment with comprehensive security, observability, and graceful degradation."}],"totalDurationMs":55582,"totalTokens":39179,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19670,"cache_read_input_tokens":14599,"output_tokens":4904,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19670},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
